-- Arsenal Chairman Peter Hill-Wood Suffers Heart Attack, Club Says
-- B y   J a m e s   C o n e
-- 2012-12-02T12:41:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-12-02/arsenal-chairman-peter-hill-wood-suffers-heart-attack-club-says.html
Arsenal Chairman Peter Hill-Woodhas
suffered a heart attack and is now making “a good recovery” in
the hospital, the Premier League soccer club said in a
statement.  “Peter was taken ill at home on Friday and is currently
being treated in hospital,” Arsenal  said on its website . “The
Club wishes Peter a full and speedy return to health.”      The 76-year-old has recently had a bout of pneumonia, the
club said.  Hill-Wood has been on the board since 1962, and took over
as chairman in 1982 after the death of his father.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Cone at 
 jcone@bloomberg.net  